  "body": "Montenegrin footballer Vasilije Šijaković Personal information Full name Vasilije Šijaković Date of birth 31 July 1929 Place of birth Nikšić , Kingdom of Yugoslavia Date of death 10 November 2003 (2003-11-10) (aged 74) Place of death Belgrade , Serbia and Montenegro Position Defender Youth career 1946–1950 Partizan Senior career* Years Team Apps ( Gls ) 1950–1952 Partizan 10 (5) 1952–1954 Red Star Belgrade 16 (2) 1954–1962 OFK Belgrade 142 (22) 1962–1963 FC Grenoble 9 (3) Total 187 (34) International career 1957–1962 Yugoslavia 11 (0) * Club domestic league appearances and goals Vasilije Šijaković ( Montenegrin Cyrillic : Василије Шијаковић; 31 July 1929 – 10 November 2003) was a Montenegrin footballer who played as a defender . He played at two World Cup Finals tournaments for Yugoslavia . Club career [ edit ] At club level, he played for the major domestic clubs, FK Partizan , Red Star Belgrade , OFK Belgrade and French Grenoble Foot 38 . International career [ edit ] Šijaković made his debut for Yugoslavia in a November 1957 FIFA World Cup qualification match against Romania and has earned a total of 11 caps, scoring no goals. His final international was a June 1962 FIFA World Cup Finals match against Czechoslovakia . [ 1 ] References [ edit ] ^ \"Player Database\" . eu-football.info . Retrieved 15 October 2020 . External links [ edit ] Vasilije Šijaković at National-Football-Teams.com Vasilije Šijaković at Reprezentacija.rs (in Serbian) v t e 1958 FIFA World Cup Team of the Tournament Media's team Goalkeeper Harry Gregg Lev Yashin Defenders Orvar Bergmark Djalma Santos Hilderaldo Bellini Nílton Santos Vasilije Šijaković Bobby Evans Bengt Gustavsson Midfielders Yuriy Voynov Horst Szymaniak Danny Blanchflower Forwards Garrincha Didi Pelé Raymond Kopa Lennart Skoglund Eddie Turnbull Helmut Rahn Just Fontaine Jean Vincent Kurt Hamrin v t e Yugoslavia squad – 1958 FIFA World Cup 1 Beara 2 Šekularac 3 Šijaković 4 Crnković 5 Tomić 6 Zebec (c) 7 Mš. Milutinović 8 Krstić 9 Boškov 10 Šantek 11 Popović 12 Petaković 13 Veselinović 14 Md. Milutinović 15 Krivokuća 16 Pašić 17 Rajkov 18 Lipošinović 19 Ognjanović 20 Radović 21 Irović 22 Jerković Coach: Tirnanić v t e Yugoslavia squad – 1962 FIFA World Cup fourth place 1 Šoškić 2 Durković 3 Jusufi 4 Radaković 5 Marković 6 Popović 7 Anković 8 Šekularac 9 Jerković 10 Galić ( c ) 11 Skoblar 12 Krivokuća 13 Svinjarević 14 Šijaković 15 Matuš 16 Mujić 17 Melić 18 Kovačević 19 Stojanović 20 Nikolić 21 Stipić 22 Ivoš Coach: Lovrić & Mihajlović v t e FK Sutjeska Nikšić – managers Šijaković ( 1968 –69) Milošević ( 1969 –70) Petković ( 1970 ) Spasojević ( 1970 –72) Drenovac ( 1972 –73) Saračević ( 1974 –75) Živadinović ( 1980 –81) Višnjevac ( 1981 –82) Đorić ( 1983 –86) Višnjevac ( 1986 –87) Spasojević ( 1989 –90) Đorić ( 1990 –91) Kovačević ( 1991 –92) Rakojević ( 1992 –93) Nikolić ( 1994 ) Rakojević ( 1994 –95) Pejović ( 1996 ) Spasojević ( 1996 –98) Bekvalac ( 1998 –99) Olarević ( 1999 –00) Giljen ( 2000 ) Starovlah ( 2000 –01) Lazarević ( 2001 ) Nenezić ( 2001 –02) Giljen c ( 2002 ) Smiljanić ( 2002 –03) Gardašević ( 2003 ) Kuzeljević ( 2003 ) Bajović ( 2004 ) Giljen c ( 2005 ) Smiljanić ( 2005 ) Nenezić ( 2006 ) Giljen ( 2006 –08) Nenezić ( 2008 ) Rakojević ( 2008 –10) Giljen c ( 2010 ) Rakojević ( 2011 ) Mijanović ( 2011 ) Lacmanović ( 2011 ) Mirković ( 2011 –12) Petrović ( 2012 ) Radojičić ( 2014 ) Tomić ( 2014 –15) Nenezić ( 2015 ) Nedović ( 2015 –16) Jovović ( 2016 –17) Rakojević ( 2017 –20) Radojičić ( 2020 ) Radović ( 2020 –21) Savović ( 2021 –22) Brnović ( 2022 –23) Janković ( 2023 ) Mijanović ( 2023 –24) Radović ( 2024 ) Savović ( 2024 –25) Jelenić ( 2025 –) (c) = caretaker manager This biographical article relating to Montenegrin association football is a stub . You can help Wikipedia by adding missing information . v t e Retrieved from \" https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Vasilije_Šijaković&oldid=1291957392 \"",
